			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1494598">
									

<p>Not everything has to be flashy and world shaking.</p>
<p>You've also not thought through the consequences.</p>
<p>Dr ██████ is in charge of arranging feedings for SCP-974, but the last batch&#8230;. The child selected looked just like his kid brother. My God, what are we doing? We're monsters. How the hell did I end up like this? I'd do anything to take it all back. Now they station me out here as punishment because they must know what I'm thinking about. What's the point?</p>
<p>Though I guess if I think about it; It's distasteful, but we have to do it. The Foundation is doing good work, even if we do have to make sad choices. I'm so glad I work here. It's so peaceful out here watching those ducks on the pond. Sure my wife left me, but I had to be dedicated to my work. There's nothing I would change. I regret nothing. It all had to be done.</p>

							</div>

								
					
