					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hurtz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1328710); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1328710&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182949" alt="Hurtz" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1328710)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hurtz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1328710); return false;" >Hurtz</a></span> <span class="odate time_1341029291 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Jun 2012 04:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1494631">
									

<p>It's not just relaxing. It puts a compulsion on you that makes you feel good about all your past decisions as well, washing away guilt and pain.</p>
<p>Think about that for a while. It's an incredibly dangerous effect, but it's completely understated in the article.</p>
<p>There are way too many things on the site that beats you in the head with every dark and twisted implication and completely kills any level of subtlety there might have been, and far too few things where you really have to sit back and let the horror soak into you.</p>
<p>I mean, we could grimdark it up and say it was discovered after noticing an increase in domestic violence in the area and theorized its existence after reviewing interviews with a local serial killer that stated that while he would feel guilty after killing someone, one trip down to his old fishing hole and he'd feel better about what he was doing right away. (It would be a pretty horrible addition though.)</p>

							</div>

								
					
